23/06/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Defence Minister Pandeli Majko said Tuesday (22 June) that a visit by his Serbia-Montenegro counterpart, Prvoslav Davinic, marks the end of the cold war between the two countries and sets the stage for a new era in bilateral relations.
Davinic agreed, saying, "Milosevic's era has passed ...
And we have to go forward, because the future is excellent."
In other news, Albanian Klan TV aired an interview Tuesday with Patrick Rock, an advisor to EU External Affairs chief Chris Patten.
Rock said political stability is the main challenge Albania faces on the road to EU integration.
(Albanian Daily News - 23/06/04;
(AFP - 22/06/04)
